problem: How many different values are represented by the following quantities? $$3^{-2}, 9^{-2}, 27^{-\frac{2}{3}}, 9\cdot81^{-1}, 243^{-\frac{4}{5}}$$
chatgpt_solution:
We have \begin{align*}
3^{-2}&=\left(\frac13\right)^2=\frac19,\\
9^{-2}&=\left(\frac13\right)^2=\frac19,\\
27^{-\frac23}&=\left(\frac13\right)^2=\frac19,\\
9\cdot81^{-1}&=9\cdot\frac{1}{81}=\frac19,\\
243^{-\frac45}&=\left(\frac{3}{3^3}\right)^{-\frac45}=\left(\frac{1}{3^2}\right)^{\frac45}=\left(\frac13\right)^{\frac85}=\left(\frac13\right)^2=\frac19.
\end{align*} All the quantities are equal to $\dfrac{1}{9}$. So, there is only $\boxed{1}$ different value represented by these quantities.
